pic1_alt: A screenshot of the National UFO Reporting Center website. The site shows a hooded figure looking up at a light in the sky. The words National UFO REporting Center appear in the center of the page, with their motto, 'Dedicated to the collection and dissemination of objective UFO data.' Below that is a button to file a report.
pic2_alt: A diagram of parts of day from the National Weather Service. The full description is available at https://www.weather.gov/lmk/twilight-types. The diagram is a circle, with 'Day' in yellow above the horizon, running from sunrise on the right through sunset on the left. The twilights are labeled just below the horizon on each side, in order they're civil, nautrical, and astronomical twilight. Night runs from roughly the end of civil twilight on either end.
